{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund rehabilitation centres to replace prison for addiction related crimes",
        "additional_details": "We believe drug addiction isn\u2019t just a personal failure \u2014 it\u2019s a neurological and social crisis. Drugs hijack the brain\u2019s reward system, making it nearly impossible to simply \u201cchoose\u201d to stop. Many commit crimes not from intent, but from impaired judgment. Yet we believe prisons only punish and isolate, ignoring the root cause. Without proper treatment, addiction can worsen behind bars. We feel it\u2019s time to replace punishment with recovery and invest in real, lasting solutions.",
        "background": "Address rising drug use and related crimes by building special secure rehab centres that act like both hospitals and prisons. Since drugs affect brain function and decision-making. These centres could provide medical treatment and structure, giving people a real opportunity to recover.",
